key_points: Gabby Petito was last seen alive in an argument involving Brian Laundrie and Merry Piglets restaurant staff in Jackson Hole, according to eyewitnesses.
Nina Celie Angelo and Matthew England, a couple from New Orleans, witnessed the altercation and reported it to Fox News Digital.
Merry Piglets confirmed Petito and Laundrie's presence at the restaurant on Aug. 27 and notified the FBI.
Angelo described Laundrie's behavior as aggressive, noting he argued with staff possibly over the bill and returned to the restaurant multiple times.
Petito apologized for Laundrie's behavior during the incident.
The restaurant manager and local law enforcement could not recall the incident; the FBI declined to comment.
The eyewitnesses connected the incident with Petito and Laundrie after seeing Utah police bodycam video.
Matthew England reported the incident to the FBI after realizing the couple in question was Petito and Laundrie.
The incident occurred approximately two weeks after a reported confrontation between Petito and Laundrie in Moab, Utah.
Petito's remains were discovered at a campsite north of Jackson Hole a few weeks later; Laundrie returned to Florida without her on Sept. 1.
